  "prompt": "I am an average student preparing for the IIT-JEE. Which test series is the best for me for free?",
  "response": "Preparing for the IIT-JEE as an average student can be a challenging but rewarding journey. While there are many paid test series available, there are also some good free resources that can help you practice effectively:\n\n1. **NTA Abhyas App**: The National Testing Agency (NTA) provides a free mock test app for JEE Main. You can access a series of tests that mimic the actual exam pattern.\n\n2. **Embibe**: Embibe offers free practice tests and personalized feedback on your performance. Their platform also provides a vast question bank for various topics.\n\n3. **Unacademy**: Unacademy frequently conducts free live tests and quizzes. You can participate in these tests to evaluate your preparation and track your progress.\n\n4. **Vedantu**: Vedantu provides free mock tests and quizzes for JEE preparation. You can take these tests to assess your understanding and readiness for the actual exam.\n\n5. **infinite Learning**: This platform offers free mock tests and practice questions specifically tailored for JEE aspirants.\n\n6. **Online IIT-JEE Test Series**: Many YouTube channels and educational websites provide free test series and question papers for practice.\n\n7. **Previous Year Papers**: Solving previous years' IIT-JEE papers is an excellent way to familiarize yourself with the exam pattern and types of questions. You can find these papers online for free.\n\nWhen selecting a test series, ensure it aligns with the JEE syllabus and provides a mix of difficulty levels. Regular practice and self-assessment will help improve your performance over time. Good luck with your preparation!",
